pp-side-by-side.jpg\"/\u003e\n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                                    \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003ch2 id=\"the-right-click-menu-and-file-explorer-are-too-simple\"\u003e\n            \u003cspan\u003e8 \u003c/span\u003e\n        \u003cspan\u003e\n                            The Right-Click Menu and File Explorer Are Too Simple\n                    \u003c/span\u003e\n       \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnyone who has used Windows 10 knows how unproductive the Windows 11 right-click context menu is. It buries many useful features behind the \u0026#34;Show more options\u0026#34; menu, requiring an extra click to access them.\u003c/p\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003eFurther, Microsoft doesn’t offer an easy way to \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/restore-classic-windows-right-click-context-menu/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003erevert to the classic Windows 10 context menu\u003c/a\u003e. As a result, your best option is to hold the \u003cstrong\u003eShift key\u003c/strong\u003e while right-clicking on anything.\u003c/p\u003e    \n                \n    \n    \n    \n                \n    \n                \n        \n                                                            \n                                                                                                                        \n                            \n    \n    \n    \u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2024/10/windows-11-context-menu-and-the-classic-context-menu.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                    